      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BELTONE BOY (4) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling off pace at this track, but prior to that won by 1.5 lengths at this track (22.75) beating Zipping Deloris in a NG on June 6. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Has ability and looks hard to stop. FLYING MONKEY'S (2) boasts a strong record this journey with 10 wins and 11 minors from 28 tries. Scored by half a length last time (22.85) in a NG over 400m at this track. Makes strong appeal on best. ELECTRIC ASSENT (6) jumped from a squeeze box last start but was quickly into stride and led throughout to score (22.15) at Gosford in a NG over 388m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Can continue on with her winning form. SEMI PEAKIN' (1) was in the money last start despite a big quote and is likely to feature again.",
